<A>__{hector stands at the well some way from the house. beatrice's garden is a madness of wild flowers, harvested by her for scents and powders. she is a remarkable woman, living as she does in the harsh male world of her time. the scented air and the dizzy sounds of the bees almost make hector swoon. he is experiencing the full, heady impact of beatrice, and it is summed up in a full blown pollen filled sneeze. he drinks at her well. the boy is beside him, still engrossed in his new shoes. hector splashes some water on his face and looks back at the house. he has some decisions to make.}
